# Copy this file to ".env" (git-ignored) and fill in your credentials.
# Full setup instructions: docs/INSTALL.md §3.

# --- RTE API (data.rte-france.com) ------------------------------------------
# 1. Create an account at https://data.rte-france.com
# 2. Create an "application" and subscribe it to each API you need (see config/rte_catalog.yaml)
# 3. Copy the application's client_id / client_secret below
# Verify with:  python -m pricemodeling rte-token
RTE_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id
RTE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret

# --- ENTSO-E Transparency API (zonal prices, load, generation, flows, REMIT) -
# Free account at https://transparency.entsoe.eu, then request API access from
# transparency@entsoe.eu and paste the token below.
ENTSOE_TOKEN=your_entsoe_token

# --- CDS (ERA5 / CMIP6) -----------------------------------------------------
# NOT set here: the CDS client reads ~/.cdsapirc (url + key). Create an account at
# https://cds.climate.copernicus.eu, accept the dataset licences, and write ~/.cdsapirc.

# --- Optional path overrides (defaults are fine for a normal checkout) -------
# POWERSIM_ROOT=/path/to/PriceModeling      # repo root (data lake / duckdb live under data/)
# POWERSIM_LAKE=/path/to/data/lake          # override the Parquet lake location
# POWERSIM_DUCKDB=/path/to/data/powersim.duckdb
